title: ORIVET 2 Pack Dog DNA Test | Comprehensive Dog Breed Test Kit, Genetic Testing, Health Risks Screen and Life Plan GenoPet+ for Canines
features: Breed Identification for Dogs: Orivet’s industry-leading Breed Identification dog DNA test screens for over 350 breeds, types, and varieties of canines. Your report will include the percentage of each breed that makes up your dog.

Genetic Health Screening: Your pet’s sample will be screened for over 250 diseases and traits. GenoPet 5.0 dog DNA test combines breed identification and health screen results to highlight the diseases that are relevant to your dog.

Easy to use: Orivet’s Collection swabs are designed to capture buccal (cheek) cells quickly and easily. This process takes less than a minute to complete. After activating and allowing time for the swabs to dry, your sample can be on its way to us in 15 minutes!

Trusted Results: For over a decade, Orivet has been trusted by veterinarians and breeders as a worldwide leader in canine genetic research. Now you can get the same innovative testing professionals use for your own dog in as little as 3 weeks!

LifePlan Included: Your Genopet 5.0 dog DNA test includes Orivet’s LifePlan. This personalized wellness plan is based on the dog breeds discovered, your dog's age, weight, gender, geographic location, and lifestyle.
description: What information will I get from this dog DNA test? -Percentage Levels of Each Breed. -Adult Weight Prediction. -Insights into Your Dog’s Personality and Behavior. -Discover heritable health risks and what to do about them. -Nutritional Suggestions for your Dog. -Routine health care advice and alerts e.g. vaccination overdue. What’s in the Kit? 2 separate packages of -Sterile DNA Collection Swabs. -Information Brochure with DNA Collection Instructions. -Self Addressed Pre-Paid Envelope. How Do I Get My Results? Results are presented in an interactive online account where you can constantly update your pet’s records such as weight, body condition, nutrition, health records and medication. You can easily share your pet’s profile with your veterinarian, health care providers, family and friends. How long can I expect to wait for my results? Once we receive your sample/s, we will send you an email confirming that your sample/s have arrived. From this date, you can expect to receive results via email within 10-14 business days. We will send another email when the sample is processing and one last one when the results are ready. In the meantime, you can login to your account to answer a few questions about your pet that will help us further customize the results to your pet.
